dataLineage.statement:
Layer was downloaded by ITOS from an email sent by the IMO. It was then analyzed by ITOS for errors. Those errors were corrected and the layer was sent back to UNOCHA as a feature class within a file geodatabase.
The following errors were found and fixed by ITOS:
1. Created and populated reference name field 2. Admin0 p-code changed to 2-letter ISO code "SL" 3. Fixed 171 gap errors and 180 overlap errors 4. Extra spaces removed from Admin4 names "Susan' s Bay", "Kagbaran Dokom B" and "Setti - Yakanday". 5. Fixed missing leading zero in Admin1 p-codes for "Southern". 6. Admin 1 p-codes for Admin4 "Turttle Islands" and "Bonthe Town" have been populated. P-codes come from admin 1 p-code portions of their admin 4 p-codes. Their missing admin 1 names were matched to their p-codes 7. Fixed 42 missing Admin2 p-codes. P-codes were matched to their admin 2 names. 8. Fixed inconsistent Admin1 attribution for Admin4 "Tasso Island". 9. Admin 1 name "Western Area" changed to "Western" to match name in Admin1 layer. 10. Admin 2 names in Admin4 matched to names in Admin2 layer. 11. Admin4 units in Admin3 "Koidu Town" incorrectly listed "Koidu Town" as the Admin2. They were given the Admin2 name "Kono". Admin4 units in Admin3 "Makeni Town" incorrectly also listed "Makeni" as the Admin2. They were given the Admin2 name "Bombali". 12. Admin3 "Koya" had p-code "SL020405" in Admin4 layer and "SL020412" in Admin3. Admin4 p-codes in "Koya" began with admin 3 p-code "SL020405". IMO has instructed ITOS that the correct p-code for Koya is "SL020412". Admin4 p-code inconsistencies have been fixed 13. Admin4 name "Turttle Islands" was misspelled and was changed to "Turtle Islands" 14. IMO has instructed ITOS to merge the following duplicates: "North Ward-Reserva", "North Ward-Kissy T", "East Ward-Messima", "Bombali Sebora - M". The truncated names have been expanded to: "North Ward-Reservation", "North Ward-Kissy Town", "East Ward-Messima", "Bombali Sebora - Makeni"
The following errors were discovered by ITOS but were not addressed in this version:
1. Two Admin4 units named "Jassende Ngoleima" exist in Admin3 "Kpaka". They have unique p-codes.
